== Preparation ==

Heat broiler to high. Bring a #medium pot{} of salted @water{} to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Core, deseed, and dice @poblano pepper{1} into ½-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}.

Place @smoky red pepper crema{2%tbsp} in a small #bowl{}. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Pasta ==

Once water is boiling, add @cavatappi pasta{6%oz} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Drain.

== Nacho Mac ’n’ Cheese ==

While pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #medium ovenproof pan{} over medium heat (use a large ovenproof pan for 4 servings). Add poblano and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add @butter{2%tbsp}, scallion whites, garlic, and @Southwest spice blend{1%tbsp}; cook, stirring, until butter melts and scallion whites are softened, ~{1%minute}.

Stir @flour{1%tbsp} into pan and cook until smooth and incorporated, ~{1%minute}. Gradually stir in @water{1/2%cup} until fully combined.

Add @cream cheese{6%tbsp} and cook, stirring, until fully incorporated and sauce has thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in @white cheddar cheese{1%cup} until melted and smooth. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Stir drained cavatappi into pan with sauce until coated. Taste and season with salt if needed. If mixture is too thick, add a splash more water.

> If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer mixture now to a #baking dish{}.

Using your hands, crush @Food Should Taste Good™ blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%oz} and evenly sprinkle over mac ’n’ cheese. Top with an even layer of @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup}.

Broil until cheese melts, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Drizzle mac ’n’ cheese with smoky red pepper crema. Top with scallion greens and as much @hot sauce{1%tsp} as you like. Serve.